cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with video disentanglement, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an unsupervised variational model, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically unsupervised learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also deals with predicting the future of independent factors, which is a problem in artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the third most likely category. The paper also involves analyzing and interpreting the learned factors, which falls under the category of multimedia, specifically video analysis, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is the fourth most likely category. Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing for interpreting the learned factors as objects in a scene, hence cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the fifth most likely category.
